## 🛠️ Installation & Usage

### Option 1: The Quick Way
1.  **Download** the `ProcessGovernor.ps1` file.
2.  **Right-Click** the file and select `Run with PowerShell`.
3.  **Accept** the Administrator prompt (Required to change system priorities).
4.  **Minimize** the window and enjoy a snappier PC!

### Option 2: Command Line (Power Users)
```powershell
git clone [https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/Windows-Process-Governor.git](https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/Windows-Process-Governor.git)
cd Windows-Process-Governor
.\ProcessGovernor.ps1

---
⚙️ Configuration
You can tweak the settings at the top of the script file to fit your needs:

$Config = @{
    # Where to save the log file
    LogFile          = "$env:TEMP\GovernorLog.txt"
    
    # Services to keep alive
    CriticalServices = @("Audiosrv", "Spooler", "wuauserv") 
    
    # Clean temp files if disk space is below this (GB)
    MinDiskSpaceGB   = 10 
}

